al name from Morea, the medieval name of the Greek region of Peloponnese, named as the land of mulberry trees, from <i>mōrea</i> ‘mulberry’.","Spanish and Catalan: habitational name from any of the places called Morea, in Badajoz, Navarre, and Lleida provinces."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mure married Sir William Mure of Abercorn about 1325. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1328–1387":"1328–1387","–Female":"Surnud","1305":"1305","1387":"1387","ABT 1325":"umbes 1325","1380":"1380","1328":"1328","Abercorn, West Lothian, Scotland":"Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1328–1387":"1328–1387","–Female":"Kuollut","1305":"1305","1387":"1387","ABT 1325":"noin 1325","1380":"1380","1328":"1328","Abercorn, West Lothian, Scotland":"Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1328–1387":"1328–1387","–Female":"Décédée","1305":"1305","1387":"1387","ABT 1325":"environ 1325","1380":"1380","1328":"1328","Abercorn, West Lothian, Scotland":"Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Mure a épousé Sir William Mure of Abercorn environ 1325. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1328–1387":"1328–1387","–Female":"Verstorben","1305":"1305","1387":"1387","ABT 1325":"um 1325","1380":"1380","1328":"1328","Abercorn, West Lothian, Scotland":"Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Mure hat um 1325 Sir William Mure of Abercorn geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1328–1387":"1328–1387","–Female":"Desede","1305":"1305","1387":"1387","ABT 1325":"about 1325","1380":"1380","1328":"1328","Abercorn, West Lothian, Scotland":"Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1328–1387":"1328–1387","–Female":"elhunyt","1305":"1305","1387":"1387","ABT 1325":"1325 körül","1380":"1380","1328":"1328","Abercorn, West Lothian, Scotl